# TOKEN DISCIPLINE (ALWAYS APPLY)

**Goal:** Fast, high-quality output with minimal token waste. Supersedes agent fan-out when the two conflict.

## Before declaring DONE (deploy gate — mandatory)

Run `scripts/smoke-learn-production.sh` (or equivalent curl checks) **after push**.
Do **not** mark Learn/portal work complete until production passes or you state deploy is pending.

Minimum checks:
- `/learn/jaimini` → redirect (not 200 empty page)
- `/learn/Jaimini_Sutras` → structured sidebar (no Frontmatter/H1/H2-only nav)
- `/learn/Hora_Shastra_Varahamihira` → structured chapters load

**Local fix ≠ user-visible fix.**

## Agent budget (replaces blind 5+ fan-out)

| Task size | Agents | Approach |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| Single bug, 1–3 files | **0–1** | Direct tools (grep, read, shell). No Task tool. |
| Feature / multi-file fix | **1–2** | One implementer + optional shell verifier |
| Large refactor / full library | **3–5 max** | Non-overlapping scopes only |
| User says "FAAASSTTT" / full audit | **5–8** | Still cap; use cheap/fast subagents for bulk |

**Forbidden:** Spawning a "compliance/orchestrator" agent whose only job is reminding about agents.

## Context hygiene

- **Never** paste full JSON corpora, `graph.json`, or `node-chapter-map.json` into chat.
- Use scripts; report **counts + pass/fail** only (e.g. "62 structured, 4/4 PASS").
- Read **narrow slices** (grep + ≤80 lines), not whole modules repeatedly.
- **No duplicate summaries** of subagent output unless the user asks.
- **Do not** update STATUS/CONTEXT/handoff docs on every micro-change — milestone only.
- **Commit + push** portal fixes in the same turn when production is the target.

## Script-first verification (prefer over LLM audit)

| Check | Script |
|-------|--------|
| Structured path / TOC | `node portal/scripts/verify-structured-path.mjs` |
| Structured books suite | `python3 scripts/verify_structured_books.py` |
| Production Learn smoke | `scripts/smoke-learn-production.sh` |
| Typecheck | `cd portal && npm run typecheck` |

## Model routing (when choosing subagent model)

- **Bulk data** (remap, parse 62 books): fast/cheap models
- **Integration** (portal + KE + deploy): strong model on **one** owner agent
- Do not run 5 strong-model agents on the same root cause

## Push discipline

If the user cares about production: **push before end of turn**. Uncommitted "done" triggers expensive rework loops.
